data.chText: 导航；确定（船、飞机、汽车等）的位置和方向
data.enText: to find your position or the position of your ship, plane, car etc. and the direction you need to go in, for example by using a map
I'll drive, and you can navigate.

data.chText: 你怎么才能设法走出森林？
data.enText: How do you navigate your way through a forest?
to sail along, over or through a sea, river etc.

data.chText: 河道变得又窄又浅，无法航行。
data.enText: The river became too narrow and shallow to navigate.

data.chText: 找到正确方法（对付困难复杂的情况）
data.enText: to find the right way to deal with a difficult or complicated situation

data.chText: 我们下一步必须设法使各级委员会予以通过。
data.enText: We next had to navigate a complex network of committees.
to find your way around on the Internet or on a particular website

simple_means.memory_skill: nav 船 + ig 走 + ate 表动词 → 驾船走 → 航海

means: 确定(船、飞机、汽车等)的位置和方向
找到正确方法(对付困难复杂的情况)

tr: travel on water propelled by wind or by other means
example: The QE2 will sail to Southampton tomorrow
He navigated his way to the altar

tr: act as the navigator in a car, plane, or vessel and plan, direct, plot the path and position of the conveyance
example: Is anyone volunteering to navigate during the trip?
Who was navigating the ship during the accident?

value.def: When someone navigates a ship or an aircraft somewhere, they decide which course to follow and steer it there. You can also say that a ship or an aircraft navigates somewhere.

example.ex: Captain Cook safely navigated his ship without accident for 100 voyages...
example.tran: 库克船长驾驶的船安全出航100次无事故。

example.ex: The purpose of the visit was to navigate into an ice-filled fiord.
example.tran: 这次出行是为了能驶入冰雪覆盖的峡湾。

example.ex: ...the new navigation system which will enable aircraft to navigate with total pinpoint accuracy.
example.tran: 将使飞机能够精确定位飞行的新导航系统

value.tran: 为(船只、飞机等)导航;确定…的航行方向;(船只、飞机等)驶向

example.ex: The expedition was wrecked by bad planning and poor navigation.
example.tran: 这次探险因计划不周和导航不利而失败。

value.def: When a ship or boat navigates an area of water, it sails on or across it.

example.ex: ...a lock system to allow sea-going craft to navigate the upper reaches of the river...
example.tran: 使海轮可以进入河流上游地区航行的河闸控制系统

example.ex: Such boats can navigate on the Nile.
example.tran: 这种船可以在尼罗河上航行。

value.def: When someone in a car navigates, they decide what roads the car should be driven along in order to get somewhere.

example.ex: When travelling on fast roads at night it is impossible to drive and navigate at the same time.
example.tran: 晚上在高速路上行驶时根本做不到边开车边找路。

example.ex: ...the relief at successfully navigating across the Golden Gate Bridge to arrive here...
example.tran: 驾车成功驶过金门桥抵达这里后的轻松

example.ex: They had just navigated their way through Maidstone on their way to the coast.
example.tran: 他们开车去海滨的路上刚刚经过了梅德斯通。

value.def: When fish, animals, or insects navigate somewhere, they find the right direction to go and travel there.

example.ex: In tests, the bees navigate back home after being placed in a field a mile away.
example.tran: 在多次试验中，放置于一英里以外田野中的蜜蜂都能飞回蜂巢。

value.tran: (鱼、动物或昆虫)找到正确的行动方向

value.def: If you navigate an obstacle, you move carefully in order to avoid hitting the obstacle or hurting yourself.

example.ex: He was not able to walk without a cane and could only navigate steps backwards...
example.tran: 没有手杖他无法走路，只能小心翼翼地向后退。

example.ex: In the corridors he let her navigate her own way round the trolleys and other obstacles...
example.tran: 在通道里，他让她自己小心地绕过小推车和其他障碍物。

example.ex: If guests wished to use the sofa, they had first to navigate around chairs in the middle of the room.
example.tran: 如果客人想坐沙发，他们得先绕过屋中间的那几把椅子。

value.def: If you manage to navigate a difficult situation, you deal with it successfully.

example.ex: During childhood each of us has to navigate a pathway through a series of developmental stages...
example.tran: 我们每个人在童年时都要经历和应对不同的成长阶段。

example.ex: This outlook helped her to navigate through her later years with success.
example.tran: 这种观念帮她安度了晚年。

value.tran: 驾驭，成功应付(困难处境)

partsOfSpeech.dec: astro 太空 + naut 船 + ics …学 →〔研究宇宙飞船〕在太空航行的科学 → 宇航学
circum 环绕 + navigate 驾驶；航海 → 环球航行
naus 船 + ea〔= ia 病〕→ 坐船不舒服 → 晕船
nause〔a〕作呕 + ate 使… → 使作呕
naut 船 + ical …的 → 船行海上 → 航海的
nav 船 + al …的 → 船的；海军的
nav 船 + ig 走 + ate 做，造成，使… → 驾船走 → 航海
nav 船 + y 表人 → 开船的人 → 海军
